<p><img height="185" width="300" src="http://www.edenhrconsulting.com/images/stories/eden-stick-figures/eden-recruit.jpg" alt="eden-recruit" style="float: right;" />Recruitment and streamlining are a business area where employers are at their most vulnerable to the risk of an employment tribunal case. At Eden HR, we try not to focus on the potential penalties for wrong doing that can be awarded at an employment tribunal, however, many of the claims raised are surrounding unfair treatment at initial selection stage and termination of employment.</p>
<p>We can ensure that your recruitment practices are robust to stand up to theÂ scrutiny of a discrimination claim whilst also aiding you in appointing the best candidate for the role.</p>
<p>Employment can be terminated for a variety of different reasons and by either party. An employee can resign from the organisation, just as the organisation can dismiss an employee. Handling such events requires consistency, transparency and (where appropriate) sensitivity.</p>
<p>As you would expect, Eden can help guide you through the recruitment and termination processes to help you hire the best available employees and protect you from potential claims when employment is terminated.</p></td>
